{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":2690,"name":"","username":"shu","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/s/e47c2d/{size}.png","created_at":"2014-10-21T12:29:28.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eHi!\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI‚Äôm working on a space game and want to create spaceship trails (like the yellow trails \u003ca href=\"http://icdn.computec.de/videos/img/medium/2014/1/55644.jpg?t=1388658056\" data-bbcode=\"true\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003ehere in this Enemy Starfighter example\u003c/a\u003e). For now I use an interval to cache the positions and orientations for the trail in a list and use it like a ringbuffer, so that it doesn‚Äôt get too long. That part works.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eBut now I need to generate some geometry for it. The effect I have in mind is to make it look as if I would extrude a quad with the trail positions. So I guess I have to generate the additional vertices in every frame. What is the best way to do this in Urho? Do I have to generate the geometry and set it in a model on a separate node in every frame? Or can I feed the trail position samples to a shader and generate the geometry on the GPU?\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:00:50.702Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":25,"reads":9,"readers_count":8,"score":126.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":490,"topic_slug":"generating-geometry-for-spaceship-trails","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"http://icdn.computec.de/videos/img/medium/2014/1/55644.jpg?t=1388658056","internal":false,"reflection":false,"clicks":6}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":131,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":2701,"name":"Yao Wei Tjong","username":"weitjong","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/weitjong/{size}/4_2.png","created_at":"2014-10-23T04:58:31.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eAny particular reason why you don‚Äôt use ParticleEmitter for the trail?\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:00:51.520Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":11,"readers_count":10,"score":2.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":490,"topic_slug":"generating-geometry-for-spaceship-trails","display_username":"Yao Wei Tjong","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"Admin","title_is_group":false,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":true,"staff":true,"user_id":4,"hidden":false,"trust_level":4,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":2702,"name":"Lasse √ñ√∂rni","username":"cadaver","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/cadaver/{size}/3_2.png","created_at":"2014-10-23T08:44:04.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eThere is no particular inbuilt feature in Urho for dynamic trail effects, but creating a programmatic model and updating its vertex buffers every frame should not create undue performance loss. After all, that‚Äôs what the particle emitters are using.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eYou can look into the 34_DynamicGeometry sample (C++ only) to see how to create models programmatically.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIf you can think of a shader-based solution that wouldn‚Äôt require to modify geometry buffers every frame, that will possibly yield better performance. The drawables don‚Äôt have the concept of their own shader data, so in this case you would have to have an unique material on the trail object and update its shader parameters. But note that you only have access to vertex and pixel shaders, not geometry.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:00:51.583Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":11,"readers_count":10,"score":2.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":490,"topic_slug":"generating-geometry-for-spaceship-trails","display_username":"Lasse √ñ√∂rni","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"Urho3D Author","title_is_group":false,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":true,"staff":true,"user_id":3,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":2705,"name":"","username":"shu","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/s/e47c2d/{size}.png","created_at":"2014-10-23T12:34:45.000Z","cooked":"\u003caside class=\"quote\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"title\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"quote-controls\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cimg alt width=\"20\" height=\"20\" src=\"https://sjc6.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/weitjong/40/4_1.png\" class=\"avatar\"\u003e weitjong:\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAny particular reason why you don‚Äôt use ParticleEmitter for the trail?\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003c/aside\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eBecause I have no experience with graphics programming and effects, I guess. \u003cimg src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/twitter/slight_smile.png?v=5\" title=\":slight_smile:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":slight_smile:\"\u003e The trail-effect in the screenshot I posted earlier looks more like some ‚Äòsolid‚Äô geometry to me, so that was my first idea. But when that doesn‚Äôt work out, I‚Äôll try particles!\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003caside class=\"quote\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"title\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"quote-controls\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cimg alt width=\"20\" height=\"20\" src=\"https://sjc6.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/cadaver/40/3_1.png\" class=\"avatar\"\u003e cadaver:\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThere is no particular inbuilt feature in Urho for dynamic trail effects, but creating a programmatic model and updating its vertex buffers every frame should not create undue performance loss.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003c/aside\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eOk, then I will do that. I just needed reassurance, that this is a good way to do this.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThanks! \u003cimg src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/twitter/slight_smile.png?v=5\" title=\":slight_smile:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":slight_smile:\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:00:51.798Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":1,"incoming_link_count":2,"reads":12,"readers_count":11,"score":12.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":490,"topic_slug":"generating-geometry-for-spaceship-trails","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":131,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,